✨Makeup for Mature Skin ✨

Makeup always should enhance our look no matter what age we are 🙌🏻

So here are a few tips which will really help giving you a direction in which you should move when you are dealing with Mature skin :

✨Always use hydration - moisturizer is fundamentally important.

✨Eye cream - Never ignore this guys , NEVER 

✨PRIMER - this is your game changer - choose hydrating one 

✨Foundation - Hydrating foundations are your best option- choose wisely 

✨Concealer- Hydrating ones are what you should be looking for : 

✅Use concealer only if you need .

✅Use minimum 

✅Blend with hands / damp sponge 

✅Not any lighter than 1/2 - 1 shade lighter than your foundation 

✅Work quickly with it - set before it dries off !

✅Lift the outer corner and then blend ( please be gentle ) 

Powder - yes , you need it but very sparingly 

Bronzer / Blusher - CREAM formulas guys - they will work in your favour ❤️

LESS IS MORE 🙌🏻 - keep that in mind !

Hope you find this useful @makeup.vitamins : like follow share

UNDER EYE CONCEALING FOR MATURE SKIN 💕

This is such a huge concern for so many of us , so in this tutorial am walking you through on how you can go about your under eye concealing : 

Please use :

✅Eye cream ( preferred the ones containing - humectants like hyaluronic acid)

✅Eye primer - especially if you like doing eye makeup & want it to stay !

✅Avoid using foundation ( or any products in excess ) - if you don’t need concealer, than slightly go over with your foundation on the under eye area .

✅Concealer shade should be 1/2 OR 1
Shade lighter than foundation 

✅For setting use @itcosmetics - bye bye pores powder.

💕FOUNDATION - TIPS & TRICKS 💕

Consider the following tips and tricks next time you go foundation shopping 🙌🏻

✅Never buy a shade which is not a exact match .

✅Find your undertone 

✅Do not online shop ( unless you know your shade ) 

✅Test the sample ( neck to chin ) 

✅Don’t overlook your skin concerns eg: dry skin might be better off with a hydrating foundation 

✅Try to wear “white “ out fit when going foundation shopping : it really shows colour best on your skin ! 

Hope these help , lot of talking in the video guys , but this also happens to be a very frequently asked question !

💕How do I Color correct 💕

Guys , I’ve tried to break down color correction for you in simple step by step process .Hope this makes it easy to understand, so here’s what I do :

✅ Identity where you need correction 

✅Start with orange corrector & use very little 

✅Take more if you need to , and then blend : finger or blender .

✅set with powder, this is really important as we don’t want the products to move .

✅Take a concealer exact match of your skin tone , and apply on top or the corrected area .

✅Blend again , now set this with powder too ! 

✅Next use foundation, and concealer ( this time lighter than your skin tone to highlight ) 

✅Finally set with powder again - now you’re base is done !

How to use POWDER FOUNDATION 💕(contour/ blusher & Highlighter)

In this tutorial Iam showing you the technique of using powder foundation particularly .

💕Start with your usual skincare 

💕Next conceal 

💕You can use powder foundation to set the under eye 

💕Using a fluffy brush , gently apply the powder foundation all over your face .( this is how I would use a powder foundation & it works very well ) 

💕switch to a smaller brush for getting to the smaller folds of the skin 

💕Next contour / Use blusher & highlighter.

💕Finish off with eye makeup

MAKEUP RULES : MUST FOLLOW 

Here are some makeup rules that you must follow no matter what everyone says !!!

✅If you have pigmentation, colour correct ! 

✅ Set your corrector with powder before using foundation or concealer 

✅Never apply foundation from the packaging directly, start by little 

✅Never apply blush directly too , take little and apply 

✅For best performance of highlighter , set your base with setting spray then go in with powder highlighter
